la: sapientia enim doctrina secundus nomen sum is et non multus sum manifestus qui autem agnita sum permaneo usque ad conspectus Dei
en: For the wisdom of doctrine is according to her name, and she is not manifest unto many, but with them to whom she is known, she continueth even to the sight of God.

la: Suo praetereo locus referatur; neque enim persono umbra ago res capit.
en: Let me now relate a matter which I omitted in it proper place, for the person involved doe not permit the deed to rest in obscurity.

la: abundo et uber urbs ingredior et facio qui non facio pater is et pater pater is rapina et praeda et divitiae is dissipo et contra firmus cogitatio iniet et hic usque ad tempus
en: And he shall enter into rich and plentiful cities: and he shall do that which his father never did, nor his fathers' fathers: he shall scatter their spoils, and their prey, and their riches, and shall forecast device against the best fenced places: and this until a time.

la: post velamentum autem secundus tabernaculum qui dico sancio sancio
en: And after the second veil, the tabernacle which is called the Holy of Holies:

la: et Iohel filius Zechri praepono is et Judas filius Sennua super civitas secundus
en: And Joel the son of Zechri their ruler, and Judas the son of Senua wa second over the city.

la: dico Dominus ad Mosen mors morior homo iste obruo is lapis omnis turba extra castrum
en: And the Lord said to Moses: Let that man die, let all the multitude stone him without the camp.

la: Abisai verus filius Sarviae percutio Edom in valles Salinaris decem et octo mille
en: And Abisai the son of Sarvia slew of the Edomites in the vale of the saltpits, eighteen thousand:

la: similis et calix postquam ceno dico hic calix novus testamentum sum in meus sanguis hic facio quotienscumque bibo in meus commemoratio
en: In like manner also the chalice, after he had supped, saying: This chalice is the new testament in my blood. This do ye, a often a you shall drink, for the commemoration of me.

la: et adhesit Domino et non recedo ab vestigium is facio mandatum is qui praecipio Dominus Mosi
en: And he stuck to the Lord, and departed not from his steps, but kept his commandments, which the Lord commanded Moses.

la: nonne iste sum sermo qui loquor ad tu in Aegyptus dico recedo ab nos ut servio Aegyptius multus enim bonus sum servio is quam morior in solitudo
en: Is not this the word that we spoke to thee in Egypt, saying: Depart from us, that we may serve the Egyptians? for it wa much better to serve them, than to die in the wilderness.

la: Sed is res longus aliter atque reor sum evenit.
en: But the result wa far different from what he had expected:

la: ideo omnis sustineo propter eligo ut et ipse salus consequor qui sum in Christus Iesus cum gloria caelestis
en: Therefore I endure all thing for the sake of the elect, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus, with heavenly glory.

la: tempus autem quo ambulo de Cadesbarne usque ad transeo torreo Zared triginta octo annus sum donec consumo omnis generatio homo bellator de castrum sicut juro Dominus
en: And the time that we journeyed from Cadesbarne till we passed over the torrent Zared, wa thirty-eight years: until all the generation of the men that were fit for war wa consumed out of the camp, a the Lord had sworn:

la: Per hiems lucubratio hic facito: ridica et palos, qui pridie in tectum posueris, siccus dolato, facula facito, stercus egerito.
en: The following is evening work for winter: Work up into vine pole and stake the wood which wa brought under cover the day before to dry out; make faggots; and clear out manure.

la: pes fatuus facilis in domus propior et homo pereo confundo ab persono possum
en: The foot of a fool is soon in his neighbour's house: but a man of experience will be abashed at the person of the mighty.

la: et manduco et saturo sum et tollo qui supero de fragmentum septem sporta
en: And they did eat and were filled: and they took up that which wa left of the fragments, seven baskets.

la: audio autem Abdemelech Aethiops vir eunuchus qui sum in domus rex qui mitto Hieremias in lacus porro rex sedeo in porto Beniamin
en: Now Abdemelech the Ethiopian, an eunuch that wa in the king's house, heard that they had put Jeremias in the dungeon: but the king wa sitting in the gate of Benjamin.

la: Dominum formido adversarius is super ipse in caelis tono Dominus iudico finis terra et do imperium rex suus et sublimo cornu christus suus
en: The adversary of the Lord shall fear him: and upon them shall he thunder in the heavens: The Lord shall judge the end of the earth, and he shall give empire to his king, and shall exalt the horn of his Christ.

la: at verus omnis Israhel qui sto per gyrus fugio ad clamor pereo dico ne fors et nos terra degluttio
en: But all Israel, that wa standing round about, fled at the cry of them that were perishing: saying: Lest perhaps the earth swallow u up also.

la: Ceterum deus filius nullus de impudicitia habeo matrem; etiam quam video habere, non nupserat.
en: But the Son of God ha a mother touched by no impuritya; even she, whom he seems to have, had never been a bride.

la: in omnis hic non sum averto furor is sed adhuc manus is extendo
en: After all these thing his indignation is not turned away, but his hand is stretched out still.

la: et manduco omnis et saturo sum et tollo sum qui supersum ille fragmentor co-finio duodecim
en: And they did all eat and were filled. And there were taken up of fragment that remained to them, twelve baskets.

la: ut venio super tu omnis sanguis iustus qui effundo sum super terra ab sanguis Abel justus usque ad sanguis Zacchariae filius Barachiae qui occido inter templum et altare
en: That upon you may come all the just blood that hath been shed upon the earth, from the blood of Abel the just, even unto the blood of Zacharias the son of Barachias, whom you killed between the temple and the altar.

la: At Iugurtha, cognosco vanitas atque imperitia legati, subdolus is augeo amentiam, missitaris supplico legatos, ipse quasi vitabundus per saltuosus locum et trames exercitus ductare.
en: Jugurtha, however, well aware of the folly and incapacity of the acting commander, craftily added to his folly and constantly sent him suppliant envoys, while he himself, a if trying to avoid an encounter, led his army through wooded place and by-ways.

la: Haris praetereo res ordo cum iustus alius volumen promatur, tum, uti spero, noster explicabitur.
en: As to the order of these events, and of those which have been mentioned before, the reader is referred to the special work of other historians, and I myself hope some day to give them in full.

la: verumtamen Tyro et Sidonius remitto sum in iudicium quam tu
en: But it shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the judgment than for you.

la: loquor sum Dominus ad Mosen dico
en: And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying:

la: qui ostendo opus lex scribo in cor suus testimonium reddo ille conscientia ipse et inter sui invicem cogitatio accuso aut etiam defendo
en: Who shew the work of the law written in their hearts, their conscience bearing witness to them: and their thought between themselves accusing or also defending one another,

la: et dico ego bonus sum sapientia fortitudo quomodo ergo sapientia pauper contemno sum et verbum is non sum audio
en: And I said that wisdom is better than strength: how then is the wisdom of the poor man slighted, and his word not heard?

la: baptisma autem habeo baptizaris et quomodo coarto usque dum perficio
en: And I have a baptism wherewith I am to be baptized. And how am I straitened until it be accomplished?

la: inpono itaque abrae suus a-scopo vinum et vas oleum et pulenta et palo et panis et caseus et proficio sum
en: And she gave to her maid a bottle of wine to carry, and a vessel of oil, and parched corn, and dry figs, and bread and cheese, and went out.

la: venio Nabuchodonosor rex Babylon ad civitas cum servio is ob-pugno is
en: And Nabuchodonosor, king of Babylon, came to the city, with his servants, to assault it.

la: emo mons Samaria ab Somer duo talentum argentum et aedifico is et voco nomen civitas quam extruxerat nomen Somer dominus mons Samaria
en: And he bought the hill of Samaria of Semer, for two talent of silver: and he built upon it, and he called the city which he built Samaria, after the name of Semer, the owner of the hill.

la: quoniam sapientia caro inimicitia sum in Deum lego enim Dei non subicio neque enim possum
en: Because the wisdom of the flesh is an enemy to God. For it is not subject to the law of God: neither can it be.

la: intro et excitas ille quoniam egredior mus de caverna suus audeo sum provocaris ad proelium
en: Go in, and awake him, for the mice, coming out of their holes, have presumed to challenge u to fight.

la: et in-crepo Iesus spiritus immundus et sano puer et reddo ille pater is
en: And Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit and cured the boy and restored him to his father.

la: sum simul Simon Petrus et Thomas qui dico Didymus et Nathanahel qui sum ab Cana Galilaea et filius Zebedaei et alius ex discipulis is duo
en: There were together: Simon Peter and Thomas, who is called Didymus, and Nathanael, who wa of Cana of Galilee, and the son of Zebedee and two others of his disciples.

la: At nunc non aliter destino quam praedicavit.
en: But, a it is, He ha so determined, a He ha proclaimed to us.

la: ecce terra Chaldeorum talis populus non sum Assur fundo is in captivitas traduco robustus is suffodio domus is pono is in ruina
en: Behold the land of the Chaldeans, there wa not such a people, the Assyrians founded it: they have led away the strong one thereof into captivity, they have destroyed the house thereof, they have, brought it to ruin.

la: voco Mosen et Aaron nox aio surgo egredior ab populus meus et tu et filius Israhel eo immolo Domino sicut dico
en: And Pharao calling Moses and Aaron, in the night, said: Arise and go forth from among my people, you and the child of Israel: go, sacrifice to the Lord a you say.

la: hic sum autem qui accipio debeo aurum et argentum et aes
en: And these are the thing you must take: Gold, and silver, and brass,

la: surgo autem Ismahel filius Nathaniae et decem vir qui sum cum is et percutio Godoliam filius Ahicam filius Saphan gladius et interfacio is qui praeficio rex Babylon terra
en: And Ismahel the son of Nathanias arose, and the ten men that were with him, and they struck Godolias the son of Ahicam, the son of Saphan with the sword, and slew him whom the king of Babylon had made governor over the land.

la: si tu volo persuadeo frater tuus filius mater tuus aut filius tuus vel filia sive uxor qui sum in sinus tuus aut amicus qui diligo ut anima tuus clam dico eo et servio diuus alienus qui ignoro tu et pater tuus
en: If thy brother the son of thy mother, or thy son, or daughter, or thy wife that is in thy bosom, or thy friend, whom thou lovest a thy own soul, would persuade thee secretly, saying: Let u go, and serve strange gods, which thou knowest not, nor thy fathers,

la: contero Dominus baculis impii virga dominor
en: The Lord hath broken the staff of the wicked, the rod of the rulers,

la: consurgo et ascendo ad gens quiesco et habito confidenter aio Dominus non ostium non vecto is solus habito
en: Arise, and go up to a nation that is at ease, and that dwelleth securely, saith the Lord: they have neither gates, nor bars: they dwell alone.

la: appareo Dominus Abram et dico is semen tuus do terra hic qui aedifico ibi altare Domino qui appareo is
en: And the Lord appeared to Abram, and said to him: To thy seed will I give this land. And he built there an altar to the Lord, who had appeared to him.

la: porro armentum qui pasco in Sarona praepono sum Setrai Saronites et super bos in valles Saphat filius Adli
en: And over the herd that fed in Saron, wa Setrai a Saronite: and over the ox in the valleys, Saphat the son of Adli:

la: DELETH adhesit lingua lacto ad palo is in sitis parvulis peto panis et non sum qui frango is
en: Daleth. The tongue of the sucking child hath stuck to the roof of his mouth for thirst: the little one have asked for bread, and there wa none to break it unto them.

la: qui cum nuntio sum David mitto in occurro is sum enim vir confundo turpis validus et mando is David maneo Hiericho donec cresco barba vester et tunc revorto
en: When this wa told David, he sent to meet them: for the men were sadly put to confusion, and David commanded them, saying: Stay at Jericho, till your beard be grown, and then return.

la: propter qui dico tu remitto is pecco multus quoniam diligo multus qui autem paruus dimitto paruus diligo
en: Wherefore, I say to thee: Many sin are forgiven her, because she hath loved much. But to whom le is forgiven, he loveth less.

la: non sitio in desero cum educo is aqua de petra produco is et scidit petra et fluo aqua
en: They thirsted not in the desert, when he led them out: he brought forth water out of the rock for them, and he clove the rock, and the water gushed out.

la: commoveo ab facies ille omnis terra ipse enim fundo orbis inmobilis
en: Let all the earth be moved at his presence: for he hath founded the world immoveable.

la: et pergo ad Emor pater suus accipio ego inquam puella hic coniunx
en: And going to Hemor his father, he said: Get me this damsel to wife.

la: aio Dominus ad Mosen
en: The Lord said to Moses:

la: et facio cum is paciscor pax et cessaris facio bestia malus de terra et qui habito in desero securus dormio in saltus
en: And I will make a covenant of peace with them, and will cause the evil beast to cease out of the land: and they that dwell in the wilderness shall sleep secure in the forests.

la: offertor is stratorius et tappetia et vasum fictilia frumentum et hordeum et farina pulentam et faba et lento frixum cicer
en: Brought him beds, and tapestry, and earthen vessels, and wheat, and barley, and meal, and parched corn, and beans, and lentils, and fried pulse,

la: et pello aries rubrico pello ianthinus et lignum setthim
en: And rams' skin dyed red, and violet skins, and setim wood:

la: cum maturus surgo fero duo uxor suus et totidem famulo cum undecim filius et transeo vadum Iaboc
en: And rising early he took his two wives, and his two handmaids, with his eleven sons, and passed over the ford of Jaboc.

la: et facio malus in conspectus Domini et ambulo in via pater suus et mater suus et in via Hieroboam filius Nabath qui peccaris facio Israhel
en: And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, and walked in the way of his father and his mother, and in the way of Jeroboam, the son of Nabat, who made Israel to sin.

la: quis do in direptio Jacob et Israhel vasto nonne Dominus ipse qui pecco et nolo in via is ambulo et non audio lex is
en: Who hath given Jacob for a spoil, and Israel to robbers? hath not the Lord himself, against whom we have sinned? And they would not walk in his ways, and they have not hearkened to his law.

la: in hypocrisis loquor mendacium et cauterio habeo suus conscientia
en: Speaking lie in hypocrisy and having their conscience seared,

la: et sum simul tabula octo bases is argenteus sedecim duo basibus per unus tabula supputas
en: And they shall be in all eight boards, and their silver socket sixteen, reckoning two socket for each board.

la: et non sum sapientia nequitia disciplina et non sum cogito peccator prudentia
en: But the learning of wickedness is not wisdom: and the device of sinner is not prudence.

la: et dico ad is hic dico Dominus exercitus Deus Israhel ecce ego mitto et ad-sumo Nabuchodonosor rex Babylon servus meus et pono thronus is super lapis iste qui abscondo et statuo solium suus super is
en: And thou shalt say to them: Thus saith the Lord of host the God of Israel: Behold I will send, and take Nabuchodonosor the king of Babylon my servant: and I will set his throne over these stone which I have hid, and he shall set his throne over them.

la: et venio de cunctus populus ad audio sapientia Salomon et ab universus rex terra qui audio sapientia is
en: And they came from all nation to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and from all the king of the earth, who heard of his wisdom.

la: tunc iubeo is introeo ubi repono sum thesaurus is et iubeo illic maneo is et constituo quis do ille de convivium suus
en: Then he ordered that she should go in where his treasure were laid up, and bade her tarry there, and he appointed what should be given her from his own table.

la: reliquiae autem is opus ad praeparatio esca abutor
en: And useth the chip of his work to dress his meat:

la: Id inpleto, postea obturato.
en: and when the cask is filled close it up.

la: loquor sum Dominus ad Mosen
en: And the Lord spoke to Moses,

la: Igitur provoco ad sacrifico obstruimus gradus pro fides conscientia nostrae, qui certus sum ad qui iste pervenio officium sub imago prostitutio et humani nomen consecratione.
en: So, when challenged to sacrifice, we stand immovable in loyalty to our conscience, certain in our knowledge whose are those service with their profane idols, and their deification of human names.

la: quomodo cado robustus et pereo arma bellicus
en: How are the valiant fallen, and the weapon of war perished?

la: cum sum enim mortalis mortuus fingo manus iniquus bonus sum enim ipse hic qui colo quia ipse quidem vivo cum sum mortalis ille autem numquam
en: For being mortal himself, he formeth a dead thing with his wicked hands. For he is better than they whom he worshippeth, because he indeed hath lived, though he were mortal, but they never.

la: Certe enim obliuiscor agitis.
en: For you certainly act a if you had forgotten.

la: et audio voco vir inter Ulai et clamo et aio Gabrihel facio intellego iste visio
en: And I heard the voice of a man between Ulai: and he called, and said: Gabriel, make this man to understand the vision.

la: idcirco hic dico Dominus ecce emitto tu ab facies terra hic annus morior adverro Dominum enim loquor sum
en: Therefore thus saith the Lord: Behold I will send thee away from off the face of the earth: this year shalt thou die: for thou hast spoken against the Lord.

la: et benedico is et appono sum ad pater suus
en: And he blessed them, and wa joined to his fathers.

la: Capreidam vel juniperus contundo in pila, libra indito, in duo congius vinum veto in vasum aeneus vel in plumbeus defervefacito.
en: Macerate capreida or juniper, add a pound of it, and boil in 2 congius of old wine in a copper or lead vessel.

la: sin autem in calvitium sive in recalvatio albus vel rufus color sum exorior
en: But if in the bald head or in the bald forehead there be risen a white or reddish colour:

la: Multa atque opportunus habes, quo facilis erro officium superes.
en: You have many opportunity easily to overcome your past mistake by good services.

la: et facio sum cum consummo Iesus sermo iste migro ab Galilaeus et venio in finis Judaea trans Jordanes
en: And it came to pas when Jesus had ended these words, he departed from Galilee and came into the coast of Judea, beyond Jordan.

la: radix meus apertus sum secus aqua et rus moror in messio meus
en: My root is opened beside the waters, and dew shall continue in my harvest.

la: recingo sum intellego et aequum invenio scientia
en: They are right to them that understand, and just to them that find knowledge.

la: Angelos quoque etiam Plato non negavit.
en: Angels again Plato ha not denied.

la: virilis ago et conforto nolo timeo neque paveo ab conspectus is quia Dominus Deus tuus ipse sum ducto tuus et non dimitto neque derelinquo tu
en: Do manfully and be of good heart: fear not, nor be ye dismayed at their sight: for the Lord thy God he himself is thy leader, and will not leave thee nor forsake thee.

la: sto rex super gradus et percutio foedus coram Domino ut ambulo post Dominum et custodio praecipio is et testimonium et caerimonia in omnis cor et in totus anima et suscito verbum foedo hic qui scribo sum in liber ille adquiesco populus pacisco
en: And the king stood upon the step: and he made a covenant with the Lord, to walk after the Lord, and to keep his commandments, and his testimonies, and his ceremonies, with all their heart, and with all their soul, and to perform the word of this covenant, which were written in that book: and the people agreed to the covenant.

la: nolo discedo ab mulier sensatus et bonus quam sortior sum in timor Dei gratia enim verecundia ille super aurum
en: Depart not from a wise and good wife, whom thou hast gotten in the fear of the Lord: for the grace of her modesty is above gold.

la: neque enim qui habeo sum dirigo sentio distribuo similis et qui non sum habeo
en: For he doth not distribute with right understanding that which wa to be had: in like manner also that which wa not to be had.

la: quandocumque pertransierit tollo tu quoniam mane diluculum pertransibit in dies et in nox et tantummodo solus vexatio intellego do auditus
en: Whensoever it shall pas through, it shall take you away: because in the morning early it shall pas through, in the day and in the night, and vexation alone shall make you understand what you hear.

la: Factum Opimii, qui inimicitiaris quaero sum ultio, paruus sequor auctoritas, et video ultio privo odium magis quam publicus vindicta data.
en: The conduct of Opimius met with a greater degree of disapproval because it wa a case of seeking revenge in a private feud, and this act of revenge wa regarded a having been committed rather in satisfaction of a personal animosity than in defence of the right of the state.

la: nunc igitur Domine Deus noster salvus nos facio de manus is ut scio omnis regnum terra quia tu sum Dominus Deus solus
en: Now therefore, O Lord our God, save u from his hand, that all the kingdom of the earth may know that thou art the Lord, the only God.

la: cum fero is de domus Abinadab qui sum in Gabaa custodio arca Dei Haio praecedo arca
en: And when they had taken it out of the house of Abinadab, who wa in Gabaa, Ahio having care of the ark of God went before the ark.

la: et audio sum qui in domus sum et convenio multus ita ut non capio neque ad ianua et loquor is verbum
en: And it wa heard that he wa in the house. And many came together, so that there wa no room: no, not even at the door. And he spoke to them the word.

la: Nunc ad res redeo.
en: Now I return to my subject.

la: pergo et capio trecenti vulpis cauda is iungo ad cauda et fax ligo in medium
en: And he went and caught three hundred foxes, and coupled them tail to tail, and fastened torch between the tails:

la: Eos fere tempus Athenae sub rex sum desierunt, qui ulter rex sum Codrus, Melanthius filius, vir non praetereundus.
en: It wa about this timea that Athens ceased to be governed by kings. The last king of Athens wa Codrus the son of Melanthus, a man whose story cannot be passed over.

la: sum Dominus cum is et sum vir in cunctus prosperus ago habito in domus dominus suus
en: And the Lord wa with him, and he wa a prosperous man in all things: and he dwelt in his master's house:

la: sed abeo patior capio teneo filius ut bene sum tu et longus vivo tempus
en: But shalt let her go, keeping the young which thou hast caught: that it may be well with thee, and thou mayst live a long time.

la: memor sum iudicium meus sic enim sum et tuus ego heri et tu hodie
en: Remember my judgment: for thine also shall be so: yesterday for me, and to day for thee.

la: et nuntio Salomon dico ecce Adonias timeo rex Salomon teneo cornu altar dico iuro ego hodie rex Salomon qui non interfacio servus suus gladius
en: And they told Solomon, saying: Behold Adonias fearing king Solomon, hath taken hold of the horn of the altar, saying: Let king Solomon swear to me this day, that he will not kill his servant with the sword.

la: et ingredior sum et possederunt is et non oboedierunt vox tuus et in lex tuus non ambulo omnis qui mando is ut facio non facio et evenio is omnis malus hic
en: And they came in, and possessed it: but they obeyed not thy voice, and they walked not in thy law: and they did not any of those thing that thou didst command them to do, and all these evil are come upon them.

la: et qui juro in templum juro in ille et in is qui inhabito in ipse
en: And whosoever shall swear by the temple sweareth by it and by him that dwelleth in it.

la: convenio omnis rex iste in unus ad aqua Merom ut pugno contra Israhel
en: And all these king assembled together at the water of Merom, to fight against Israel.

la: in magnus autem domus non solus sum vasum aureus et argenteus sed et ligneus et fictilia et quidam quidem in honor quidam autem in contumelia
en: But in a great house there are not only vessel of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of earth: and some indeed unto honour, but some unto dishonour.

la: et congrego contra is vir et facio sum princeps latro cum interfacio is David abeo Damascus et habito ibi et constituo is rex in Damascus
en: And he gathered men against him, and he became a captain of robbers, when David slew them of Soba: and they went to Damascus, and dwelt there, and they made him king in Damascus.

la: sed et servio Hiram cum servio Salomon affero aurum de Ophir et lignum thyinus et gemma pretiosus
en: And the servant also of Hiram, with the servant of Solomon, brought gold from Ophir, and thyine trees, and most precious stones:

la: Q. Catulus, et alius virtus et bellum Cimbricus gloria, qui ille cum Marius communis fuerat, celeberrimus, cum ad mors conquireretur, concludo sui locus nuper calx harena perpolio inlatoque igni, qui vis odor excitaret, simul exitial haurio spiritu, simul includo suus mors magis veto quam arbitrium inimicus obiit.
en: Then there wa Quintus Catulus, renowned for his virtue in general and for the glory, which he had shared with Marius, of having won the Cimbrian war; when he wa being hunted down for death, he shut himself in a room that had lately been plastered with lime and sand; then he brought fire that it might cause a powerful vapour to issue from the plaster, and by breathing the poisonous air and then holding his breath he died a death according rather with his enemy wish than with their judgement.

la: VII. Fundi suburbanus arbustus magnus convenio habere; et lignum et virga venio possunt, et dominus sum qui utatur.
en: VII. It is especially desirable to have a plantation on a suburban farm, so that firewood and faggot may be sold, and also may be furnished for the master use.

la: mitto autem ad ego secundus verbum hic per quattuor vicis et respondeo is iuxta sermo prior
en: And they sent to me according to this word, four times: and I answered them after the same manner.

la: facio et lucerna septem cum emunctorium suus et vasum ubi qui emungo sum extinguuntur de aurum mundus
en: He made also the seven lamp with their snuffers, and the vessel where the snuffings were to be put out, of the purest gold.

la: et aio Ionathan ad David quicumque dico ego anima tuus facio tu
en: And Jonathan said to David: Whatsoever thy soul shall say to me, I will do for thee.

la: Quippe C. Velleius, honoro inter ille trecenti et sexa_ginta iudex locus ab Cn. Pompejus lectus, idem Marcius Brutus atque Ti. Nero praefectus fabrum, vir nullus secundus, in Campania digressus Nero ab Neapoli, qui ob singularis cum is amicitia pars adjuto fuerat, gravis iam aetas et corpus cum comes sum non posset, gladius sui ipse transfixit.
en: Gaius Velleius, chosen to a most honourable position among the three hundred and sixty judgesb by Gnaeus Pompey, prefect of engineer under Pompey, Marcus Brutus, and Tiberius Nero, and a man second to none, on the departure from Naples of Nero, whose partisan he had been on account of his close friendship, finding himself unable to accompany him on account of his age and infirmities, ran himself through with his sword in Campania.

la: calathus unus ficus bonus habeo nimis ut soleo ficus sum primus tempus et calathus unus ficus habeo mala nimis qui comedo non possum is qui sum malus
en: One basket had very good figs, like the fig of the first season: and the other basket had very bad figs, which could not be eaten, because they were bad.

la: dico filius Israhel per tero gradior via et si bibo aqua tuus nos et pecus noster do qui iustus sum nullus sum in pretium difficultas tantus velociter transeo
en: And the child of Israel said: We will go by the beaten way: and if we and our cattle drink of thy waters, we will give thee what is just: there shall be no difficulty in the price, only let u pas speedily.

la: qui credo Deo ad-tendo mandatum et qui confido in ille non minoro
en: He that believeth God, taketh heed to the commandments: and he that trusteth in him, shall fare never the worse.

la: et sepelio primogenitus qui percutio Dominus nam et in diuus is exerceo ultio
en: Who were burying their firstborn, whom the Lord had slain (upon their god also he had executed vengeance,)

la: scribo sum enim perdo sapientia sapiens et prudentia prudens reprobo
en: For it is written: I will destroy the wisdom of the wise: and the prudence of the prudent I will reject

la: Sic et Epicurus omnis cruciatus dolor depretiat, modicus quidem contemptibilis pronuntiando, magnus verus non diuturnum.
en: That is why Epicurus make light of all torture and pain; if it is slight, he says, you may despise it, if it is great it will not be long.

la: et voco omnis amicus suus et dico ille recedo somnus ab oculus meus et concaedes et corruo cor prae sollicitudo
en: And he called for all his friends, and said to them: Sleep is gone from my eyes, and I am fallen away, and my heart is cast down for anxiety:

la: et sabbata meus sanctifico ut sum signum inter ego et tu et scio quia ego Dominus Deus vester
en: And sanctify my sabbaths, that they may be a sign between me and you: and that you may know that I am the Lord your God.

la: qui si dico in cor tuus quare venio ego hic propter multitudo iniquitas tuus revelo sum verecundus tuus polluo sum planta tuus
en: And if thou shalt say in thy heart: Why are these thing come upon me? For the greatness of thy iniquity, thy nakedness is discovered, the sol of thy foot are defiled.

la: sed pretiosus sanguis quasi agnus incontaminatus et immaculatus Christus
en: But with the precious blood of Christ, a of a lamb unspotted and undefiled

la: venio autem Numenius et qui cum is sum ab urbs Roma habeo epistula rex et regio scribo in qui contineo hic
en: And Numenius, and they that had been with him, came from the city of Rome, having letter written to the kings, and countries, the content whereof were these:

la: et nunc ecce manus Domini super tu et sum caecus non video sol usque ad tempus et confestim cado in is caligo et tenebra et circumeo quaero qui is manus do
en: And now behold, the hand of the Lord is upon thee: and thou shalt be blind, not seeing the sun for a time. And immediately there fell a mist and darkness upon him: and going about, he sought some one to lead him by the hand.

la: ubi sum ergo nunc praestolatio meus et patientia meus quis considero
en: Where is now then my expectation, and who considereth my patience?

la: succido saltus is aio Dominus qui supputaris non possum multiplico sum super lucustas et non sum is numerus
en: They have cut down her forest, saith the Lord, which cannot be counted: they are multiplied above locusts, and are without number.

la: si igitur praeputium justitia lex custodio nonne praeputium ille in circumcisio reputo
en: If then, the uncircumcised keep the justice of the law, shall not this uncircumcision be counted for circumcision?

la: nunc autem quaero ego interficio homo qui veritas tu loquor sum quam audio ab Deo hic Abraham non facio
en: But now you seek to kill me, a man who have spoken the truth to you, which I have heard of God. This Abraham did not.

la: ab inimicus tuus separaris et ab amicus tuus ad-tendo
en: Separate thyself from thy enemies, and take heed of thy friends.

la: Eos multitudo in unus cogo atque paulatim consuefacio ordo habere, signum sequi, imperium observare, item alius militaris facere.
en: He mustered a large number of them in one place and gradually trained them to keep ranks, follow the standards, obey orders, and perform the other duty of soldiers.

la: transeo Iepthae ad filius Ammon ut pugno contra is qui trado Dominus in manus is
en: And Jephte passed over to the child of Ammon to fight against them: and the Lord delivered them into his hands.

la: egredior et video filia Sion rex Salomon in diadema quo corono is mater suus in dies disponsio ille et in dies laetitia chordus is
en: Go forth, ye daughter of Sion, and see king Solomon in the diadem, wherewith his mother crowned him in the day of the joy of his heart.

la: si autem dico malus servus ille in cor suus mora facio dominus meus venio
en: But if that evil servant shall say in his heart: My lord is long a coming:

la: obsecro itaque tu ego vincio in Domino ut dignus ambulo vocatio qui voco sum
en: I therefore, a prisoner in the Lord, beseech you that you walk worthy of the vocation in which you are called:

la: Itaque non sine foro, non sine macello, non sine balneis, tabernis, officinis, stabulis, nundo vester ceter commercium cohabitamus in hic saeculo.
en: So, not without your forum, not without your meat-market, not without your baths, shops, factories, your inn and market-days, and the rest of the life of buying and selling, we live with you'in this world.

la: et nunc Domine tollo quaeso anima meus ab ego quia bonus sum ego mors quam vito
en: And now, O Lord, I beseech thee take my life from me: for it is better for me to die than to live.

la: Iosaphat filius Asum regno coepio super Judas annus quartum Ahab rex Israhel
en: But Josaphat, the son of Asa, began to reign over Juda, in the fourth year of Acbab, king of Israel.

la: Timotheus autem confugio in Gazara praesidium munio qui praesum Caereas
en: But Timotheus fled into Gazara, a strong hold where Chereas wa governor.

la: et loquor sum ad Ephron circumsto plebs quaeso ut audio ego do pecunia pro ager suscipio is et sic sepelio mortuus meus in is
en: And he spoke to Ephron, in the presence of the people: I beseech thee to hear me: I will give money for the field: take it, and so I will bury my dead in it.

la: qui aio invenio gratia ante oculus tuus dominus ego qui consolo sum ego et loquor sum ad cor ancilla tuus qui non sum similis unus puellaris tuus
en: And she said: I have found grace in thy eyes, my lord, who hast comforted me, and hast spoken to the heart of thy handmaid, who am not like to one of thy maids.

la: et converto cor pater ad filius et cor filius ad pater is ne fors venio et percutio terra anathema
en: And he shall turn the heart of the father to the children, and the heart of the child to their fathers: lest I come, and strike the earth with anathema.

la: et atrium magnus rotundus tres ordo de lapis seco et unus ordo dolo cedrus necnon et in atrium domus Domini interior et in porticus domus
en: And the great court wa made round with three row of hewed stones, and one row of plank of cedar, which also wa observed in the inner court of the house of the Lord, and in the porch of the house.

la: et cum dies facio sum voco discipulus suus et eligo duodecim ex ipse qui et apostolus nomino
en: And when day wa come, he called unto him his disciples: and he chose twelve of them (whom also he named apostles):

la: maledico terra Meroz dico angelus Domini maledico habitator is quia non venio ad auxilium Domini in adjutorium fortis is
en: Curse ye the land of Meroz, said the angel of the Lord: curse the inhabitant thereof, because they came not to the help of the Lord, to help his most valiant men.

la: et affero caput Hisboseth ad David in Hebrus dico ad rex ecce caput Hisboseth filius Saul inimicus tuus qui quaero anima tuus et do Dominus dominus meus rex ultio hodie de Saul et de semen is
en: And they brought the head of Isboseth to David to Hebron: and they said to the king: Behold the head of Isboseth the son of Saul thy enemy who sought thy life: and the Lord hath revenged my lord the king this day of Saul, and of his seed.

la: exeo ergo daemonium ab homo et intro in porcus et impetus abeo grex per praeceps in stagnum et suffoco sum
en: The devil therefore went out of the man and entered into the swine. And the herd ran violently down a steep place into the lake and were stifled.

la: Breve ab hic intercedo spatium, cum C. Caesar ante alius provincia ad viso obeo in Syria missus, convenio prior Ti. Nerone, qui omnis honor ut superus habuit, tam varius sui ibi gessit, ut neque laudo magnus neque vituperaturum mediocris materia deficiat.
en: Shortly after this Gaius Caesar, who had previously made a tour of other provinces, but only a a visitor, wa dispatched to Syria. On his way he first paid his respect to Tiberius Nero, whom he treated with all honour a his superior. In his province he conducted himself with such versatility a to furnish much material for the panegyrist and not a little for the critic.

la: dico ad turba recedo ab tabernaculis homo impii et nolo tango qui ad is pertineo ne involvo in peccatum is
en: He said to the multitude: Depart from the tent of these wicked men, and touch nothing of theirs, lest you be involved in their sins.

la: et ecce talentum plumbum porto et ecce mulier unus sedeo in medium amphora
en: And behold a talent of lead wa carried, and behold a woman sitting in the midst of the vessel.

la: venio autem et de Beniamin et de Judas ad praesidium in quo moror David
en: And there came also of the men of Benjamin, and of Juda to the hold, in which David abode.

la: pono thronus regnum tuus super Israhel in sempiternus sicut loquor sum David pater tuus dico non aufero de genus tuus vir de solium Israhel
en: I will establish the throne of thy kingdom over Israel for ever, a I promised David, thy father, saying: There shall not fail a man of thy race upon the throne of Israel.

la: Si ita feceris, et grossus non cado et fici scabrae non fio et multus ferax erunt.
en: If you do this the fruit will not drop prematurely, the tree will not be scaly, and they will be much more productive.

la: dico is Iesus Marium converro ille dico is rabboni qui dico magister
en: Jesus saith to her: Mary. She turning, saith to him: Rabboni (which is to say, Master).

la: qui soror puer volo inquam ut vado et voco tu hebraeam mulier qui nutrio possum infantulis
en: And the child's sister said to her: Shall I go, and call to thee a Hebrew woman, to nurse the babe?

la: Nam plerus jaculus tormentum aut manus emitto vulnero pario periculum sed fama inparis bonus atque ignavus erant.
en: for javelin hurled from engine or by hand wounded quite a few, and brave men and coward shared equal danger but unequal repute.

la: Cyrenensis tardus iere.
en: Those from Cyrene went more slowly.

la: ipse aries in frustum concaedes caput is et artus et adipem adolesco ignis
en: And cutting the ram into pieces, the head thereof, and the joints, and the fat he burnt in the fire.

la: ego quoque in interitus vester rideo et subsanno cum tu qui timeo advenio
en: I also will laugh in your destruction, and will mock when that shall come to you which you feared.

la: mortariolum aureus appendo decem siclos plenus incensum
en: A little mortar of gold weighing ten sicles full of incense:

la: audio quia ego dico tu vado et venio ad tu si diligo ego gaudeo utique quia vado ad Patrem quia Pater magnus ego sum
en: You have heard that I said to you: I go away, and I come unto you. If you loved me you would indeed be glad, because I go to the Father: for the Father is greater than I.

la: similis et facio bonus manifestus sum et qui aliter sui habeo abscondo non possum
en: In like manner also good deed are manifest: and they that are otherwise cannot be hid.

la: an divitiae bonitas is et patientia et longanimitas contemno ignoro quoniam benignitas Dei ad paenitentia tu adduco
en: Or despisest thou the rich of his goodness and patience and longsuffering? Knowest thou not that the benignity of God leadeth thee to penance?

la: Id Varus per vir is gens fidelis clarus nominis, Segesten, indico Postulabat etiam vincio socios.
en: This wa disclosed to Varus through Segestes, a loyal man of that race and of illustrious name, who also demanded that the conspirator be put in chains.

la: et ut sapientia habeo offero sacrificium dedicatio et consummatio templum
en: For he treated wisdom in a magnificent manner: and like a wise man, he offered the sacrifice of thc dedication, and of the finishing of the temple.

la: et respondeo unus de senex dico ego hic qui amingo sum stola albus qui sum et unde venio
en: And one of the ancient answered and said to me: These that are clothed in white robes, who are they? And whence came they?

la: neque elevo cor is in superbia super frater suus neque declino in pars dexter vel sinistra ut longus tempus regno ipse et filius is super Israhel
en: And that his heart be not lifted up with pride over his brethren, nor decline to the right or to the left, that he and his son may reign a long time over Israel.

la: sed et Saul abeo in domus suus in Gabaath et abeo cum is pars exercitus qui tango Deus cor
en: Saul also departed to his own house in Gabaa: and there went with him a part of the army, whose heart God had touched.

la: et praecipio rex Hieremahel filius Ammelech et Saraiae filius Ezrihel et Selemiae filius Abdehel ut comprehendo Baruch scribo et Hieremias propheta abscondo autem is Dominus
en: And the king commanded Jeremiel the son of Amelech, and Saraias the son of Ezriel, and Selemias the son of Abdeel, to take up Baruch the scribe, and Jeremias the prophet: but the Lord hid them.

la: ideo enim et tribuo praestas minister enim Dei sum in hic ipse servio
en: For therefore also you pay tribute. For they are the minister of God, serving unto this purpose.

la: et usque ad princeps fortitudo magnifico sum et ab is fero jugo sacrificium et deicio locus sanctificatio is
en: And it wa magnified even to the prince of the strength: and it took away from him the continual sacrifice, and cast down the place of his sanctuary.

la: frater et si praeoccupo sum homo in aliquis delinquo tu qui spirital sum huiusmodi instruo in spiritus lenitas considero tu ipse ne et tu tento
en: Brethren, and if a man be overtaken in any fault, you, who are spiritual, instruct such a one in the spirit of meekness, considering thyself, lest thou also be tempted.

la: hic sum officium familia Meraritaris et ministerium in tabernaculum foedo sum sub manus Ithamar filius Aaron sacerdos
en: This is the office of the family of the Merarites, and their ministry in the tabernacle of the covenant: and they shall be under the hand of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.

la: addo quoque Iob ad-sumo parabola suus et dico
en: Job also added, taking up his parable, and said:

la: eo igitur promptus de caelum habeo adiutor et misero is Dominum
en: So they went on courageously, having a helper from heaven, and the Lord, who shewed mercy to them.

la: fero omnis aurum et argentum et universus vasum qui invenio sum in domus Domini et in thesaurus rex et obses et revorto sum Samaria
en: And he took all the gold and silver, and all the vessel that were found in the house of the Lord, and in the king's treasures, and hostages, and returned to Samaria.

la: super uber plango super regio desiderabilis super vinea fertilis
en: Mourn for your breasts, for the delightful country, for the fruitful vineyard.

la: et sum velut filius Altissimi obaudio et misereo tuus magis quam mater
en: And thou shalt be a the obedient son of the most High, and he will have mercy on thee more than a mother.

la: Gedor quoque et Ahio et Zacher
en: And Gedor, and Ahio, and Zacher, and Macelloth:

la: dico ad pater hic solus ego praesto qui deprecor dimitto ego ut duo mensis circumeo mons et plango virginitas meus cum sodal meus
en: And she said to her father: Grant me only this, which I desire: Let me go, that I may go about the mountain for two months, and may bewail my virginity with my companions.

la: et postquam impleo sum dies purgatio is secundus lex Mosi fero ille in Hierusal ut sisto is Domino
en: And after the day of her purification, according to the law of Moses, were accomplished, they carried him to Jerusalem, to present him to the Lord:

la: qui aio is ecce sum vir Dei in civitas hic vir nobilis omnis qui loquor absque ambiguitas venio nunc ergo eo illic si fors indico nos de via noster propter quam venio
en: And he said to him: Behold there is a man of God in this city, a famous man: all that he saith, cometh certainly to pass. Now, therefore, let u go thither, perhaps he may tell u of our way, for which we are come.

la: scribo ergo qui video et qui sum et qui oportet fio post hic
en: Write therefore the thing which thou hast seen: and which are: and which must be done hereafter.

la: hic dico Sennacherib rex Assyrius in quo habeo fiducia sedeo ob-sedeo in Hierusal
en: Thus saith Sennacherib king of the Assyrians: In whom do you trust, that you sit still besieged in Jerusalem?

la: signum et opus qui facio in medium Aegyptius Pharao rex et universus terra is
en: The sign and work which he did in the midst of Egypt to king Pharao, and to all his land,

la: et regredior ab monumentum nuntio hic omnis ille undecim et ceterus omnis
en: And going back from the sepulchre, they told all these thing to the eleven and to all the rest.

la: tunc aio homo extendo manus tuus et extendo et restituo sum sanitas sicut alter
en: Then he saith to the man: Stretch forth thy hand; and he stretched it forth, and it wa restored to health even a the other.

la: et quomodo Mardocheus iudaici genus secundus ab rex Asuero sum et magnus inter Judaei et acceptabilis plebs frater suus quaero bonus populus suus et loquor is qui ad pax suus semen pertineo
en: And how Mardochai of the race of the Jews, wa next after king Assuerus: and great among the Jews, and acceptable to the people of his brethren, seeking the good of his people, and speaking those thing which were for the welfare of his seed.

la: nonne hic qui moror in vinum et studeo calix epoto
en: Surely they that pas their time in wine, and study to drink off their cups.

la: qui ambulo simplex salvus sum qui perverto ingredior via concaedes semel
en: He that walketh uprightly, shall be saved: he that is perverse in his ways, shall fall at once.

la: et dico ille bene irritus facio praeceptum Dei ut traditio vester servo
en: And he said to them: Well do you make void the commandment of God, that you may keep your own tradition.

la: dico ergo is ubi sum Pater tuus respondeo Iesus neque ego scio neque Patrem meus si ego scio forsitan et Patrem meus scio
en: They said therefore to him: Where is thy Father? Jesus answered: Neither me do you know, nor my Father. If you did know me, perhaps you would know my Father also.

la: et nubes qui cum impero sum ab Deo perambularis universus orbis perficio qui impero sum is
en: And the clouds, when God commandeth them to go over the whole world, do that which is commanded them.

la: Qui cum sto in medium eorum, ait: Sic fatuus filius Israel, non iudicantes, neque qui verus sum cognoscentes, condemno filia Israel?
en: But he standing in the midst of them, said: Are ye so foolish, ye child of Israel, that without examination or knowledge of the truth, you have condemned a daughter of Israel?

la: fleo autem omnis et plango ille at ille dico nolo fleo non sum morior sed dormio
en: And all wept and mourned for her. But he said: Weep not. The maid is not dead, but sleepeth.

la: applico Aaron et filius is ad foris tabernaculum testimonium et lotos aqua
en: And thou shalt bring Aaron and his son to the door of the tabernacle of the testimony, and having washed them with water,

la: cum audio sonitus gradior in cacumen pirus tunc egredior ad bellum egredior sum enim Deus ante tu ut percutio castrum Philisthim
en: And when thou shalt hear the sound of one going in the top of the pear trees, then shalt thou go out to battle. For God is gone out before thee to strike the army of the Philistines.

la: et eicio sacerdos Domini filius Aaron atque Levites et facio tu sacerdos sicut omnis populus terra quicumque venio et initio manus suus in taurus in bos et in aries septem fio sacerdos is qui non sum dius
en: And you have cast out the priest of the Lord, the son of Aaron, and the Levites: and you have made you priests, like all the nation of the earth: whosoever cometh and consecrateth his hand with a bullock of the herd, and with seven rams, is made a priest of those who are no gods.

la: facio quoque domus sanctus sancio longitudo iuxta latitudo domus cubitum viginti et latitudo similis viginti cubitum et lamminis aureus tego is quasi talentum sescenti
en: He made also the house of the holy of holies: the length of it according to the breadth of the temple, twenty cubits, and the breadth of it in like manner twenty cubits: and he overlaid it with plate of gold, amounting to about six hundred talents.

la: At Catilina non segnis conor obiit, quam scelus conor consilium inierat: quippe fortis dimico qui spiritus supplicium debuerat, proelium reddidit.
en: As for Catiline, he proceeded to carry out his criminal undertaking with a much energy a he had shown in planning it. Fighting with desperate courage, he gave up in battle the life which he had forfeited to the executioner.

la: ad perpetro fraudo tam in bos quam in asinus et ovum atque vestimentum et quisquis damnum infero possum ad deus uterque causa pervenio et si ille judico duplus restituo propior suus
en: To do any fraud, either in ox, or in ass, or sheep, or raiment, or any thing that may bring damage: the cause of both party shall come to the gods: and if they give judgment, he shall restore double to his neighbour.

la: et castrametor sum Saul in Gabaa Achilae qui sum ex adverso solitudo in via David autem habito in desero video autem qui venio Saul post sui in desertum
en: And Saul encamped in Gabaa Hachila, which wa over against the wilderness in the way: and David abode in the wilderness. And seeing that Saul wa come after him into the wilderness,

la: et sic sum ruina equus et mulus camelis et asinus et omnis iumentum qui sum in castrum ille sicut ruina hic
en: And the destruction of the horse, and of the mule, and of the camel, and of the ass, and of all the beasts, that shall be in those tents, shall be like this destruction.

la: Patres conscripti, Micipsa pater meus morior ego praecipio ut regnum Numidia tantummodo procuratio existumaris meam, ceterum ius et imperium is penis tu esse; simul eniteo domus militia quam magnus usus sum populus Romano, tu ego cognatorum, tu affinis locus ducerem: si is fecissem, in vester amicitia exercitum, divitias, munimentum regnum ego habiturum.
en: Members of the Senate, my father Micipsa admonished me on his deathbed to think that I had charge only of the administration of the kingdom of Numidia, whereas the right and authority are in your control; at the same time, he admonished me to strive to be a helpful a possible to the Roman people in peace and in war and to regard you a my kindred and relatives. He declared that if I did this, I would have in your friendship an army, wealth, and a safeguard for my kingdom.

la: Qui enim scio illum, intellego possum non nisi grandis aliqui bonus ab Nero damnatum.
en: One who know Nero can understand that, unless a thing were good'and very good'it wa not condemned by Nero.

la: filius autem Caath non do plaustrum et bos quia in sanctuarium servio et onus proprius porto umerus
en: But to the son of Caath he gave no wagon or oxen: because they serve in the sanctuary and carry their burden upon their own shoulders.

la: arripio filius suus primogenitus qui regno sum pro is offero holocaustum super murus et facio sum indignatio magnus in Israhel statim recedo ab is et revorto sum in terra suus
en: Then he took his eldest son, that should have reigned in his stead, and offered him for a burnt offering upon the wall: and there wa great indignation in Israel, and presently they departed from him, and returned into their own country.

la: et sum in dies ille non adicio residuus Israhel et hic qui fugio de domus Jacob innitor super is qui percutio is sed innitor super Dominum Sanctum Israhel in veritas
en: And it shall come to pas in that day, that the remnant of Israel, and they that shall escape of the house of Jacob, shall lean no more upon him that striketh them: but they shall lean upon the Lord the Holy One of Israel, in truth.

la: ut cum co-medeor et satio sum benedico Domino Deo tuus pro terra bonus quam do tu
en: That when thou hast eaten, and art full, thou mayst bless the Lord thy God for the excellent land which he hath given thee.

la: zelo autem Judaeus ad-sumo de vulgo vir quidam malus et turba facio concito civitas et assisto domo Iason quaero is produco in populus
en: But the Jews, moved with envy and taking unto them some wicked men of the vulgar sort and making a tumult, set the city in an uproar: and besetting Jason's house, sought to bring them out unto the people.

la: beatus homo qui audio ego qui vigilo ad foris meus cottidie et observo ad postis ostium meus
en: Blessed is the man that heareth me, and that watcheth daily at my gates, and waiteth at the post of my doors.

la: et relinquo ille abeo foras extra civitas in Bethaniam ibi maneo
en: And leaving them, he went out of the city into Bethania and remained here.

la: regina auster surgo in iudicium cum generatio iste et condemno is quia venio ab finis terra audio sapientia Salomon et ecce multus quam Salomon hic
en: The queen of the south shall rise in judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: because she came from the end of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and behold a greater than Solomon here.

la: revorto et misereo noster depono iniquitas noster et proicio in profundum mare omnis pecco noster
en: He will turn again, and have mercy on us: he will put away our iniquities: and he will cast all our sin into the bottom of the sea.

la: et levo oculus meus et video et ecce vir et in manus is funiculus mensor
en: And I lifted up my eyes, and saw, and behold a man, with a measuring line in his hand.

la: Accipe nunc, M. Vinici, tantus in bellum ducem, quantus in pax video principem.
en: Listen now, Marcus Vinicius, to the proof that Caesar wa no le great in war a a general than you now see him in peace a an emperor.

la: tertius autem annus regnum suus mitto de princeps suus Benail et Obdiam et Zacchariam et Nathanahel et Micheam ut doceo in civitas Judas
en: And in the third year of his reign, he sent of his prince Benhail, and Abdias, and Zacharias, and Nathanael, and Micheas, to teach in the cite of Juda:

la: harena mare et pluvia gutta et dies saeculis quis dinumero altitudo caelum et latitudo terra et profundum abyssus quis metior sum
en: Who hath numbered the sand of the sea, and the drop of rain, and the day of the world? Who hath measured the height of heaven, and the breadth of the earth, and the depth of the abyss?

la: reporto igitur Sadoc et Abiathar arca Dei Hierusal et maneo ibi
en: So Sadoc and Abiathar carried back the ark of God into Jerusalem: and they tarried there.

la: gloria sapio possideo stultor exaltatio ignominia
en: The wise shall posse glory: the promotion of fool is disgrace.

la: mitto rex Israhel ad locus qui dico is vir Dei et praeoccupo is et observo sui ibi non semel neque bis
en: And the king of Israel, sent to the place which the man of God had told him, and prevented him, and looked well to himself there not once nor twice.

la: nunc igitur ego Nabuchodonosor laudo et magnifico et glorifico Rex caelum quia omnis opus is verus et via is iudicium et gradior in superbia possum humiliaris
en: Therefore I, Nabuchodonosor, do now praise, and magnify, and glorify the King of heaven: because all his work are true, and his way judgments, and them that walk in pride he is able to abase.

la: et ad populus sic loquor sum hic dico Dominus Deus Israhel trans fluvius habito pater vester ab initium Tharis pater Abraham et Nahor servio diuus alienus
en: And he spoke thus to the people: Thus saith the Lord the God of Israel: Your father dwelt of old on the other side of the river, Thare the father of Abraham, and Nachor: and they served strange gods.

la: similis sum puer sedeo in forum et loquor ad invicem et dico canto tu tibia et non saltastis lamento et non ploro
en: They are like to child sitting in the marketplace and speaking one to another and saying: We have piped to you, and you have not danced: we have mourned, and you have not wept.

la: sum et alius infirmitas malus quam video sub sol divitiae conservo in malus dominus suus
en: There is also another grievous evil, which I have seen under the sun: rich kept to the hurt of the owner.

la: et observo custodio Domini Dei tuus ut ambulis in via is et custodio caerimonia is et praecipio is et iudicium et testimonium sicut scribo sum in lex Mosi ut intellego universus qui facio et quicumque tu verto
en: And keep the charge of the Lord thy God, to walk in his ways, and observe his ceremonies, and his precepts, and judgments, and testimonies, a it is written in the law of Moses: that thou mayst understand all thou dost, and whithersoever thou shalt turn thyself:

la: habeo autem semper Judas caris ex animus sum verus inclino
en: And Judas wa always dear to him from the heart, and he wa well affected to the man.

la: viginti quinque annus sum Ioatham cum regno coepio et sedecim annus regno in Hierusal nomen mater is Hierusa filia Sadoc
en: Joatham wa five and twenty year old when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen year in Jerusalem: the name of his mother wa Jerusa the daughter of Sadoc.

la: aedes Levitaris qui in urbs sum semper possum redimo
en: The house of Levites, which are in cities, may always be redeemed.

la: musica in luctus importunus narratio flagello et doctrina in omnis tempus sapientia
en: A tale out of time is like music in mourning: but the stripe and instruction of wisdom are never out of time.

la: Pharisaeus autem coepio intra sui reputo dico quare non baptizo sum ante prandium
en: And the Pharisee began to say, thinking within himself, why he wa not washed before dinner.

la: Qui oleo legerint, omnis juro ad dominus aut ad custos sui oleo non surripio neque quisquam suus dolus malus is oletas ex fundo L. Manli.
en: All gatherer will take an oath before the owner or his representative that they have not stolen olives, nor ha anyone with their connivance stolen olive from the estate of Lucius Manlius during that harvest;

la: Et ipse paucus dies idem proficiscor est, iubeo ab senatus Italia decedere.
en: A few days, later he himself set out for the same destination, having been ordered by the senate to leave Italy.

la: lux iustor laetifico lucerna autem impii extinguetur
en: The light of the just giveth joy: but the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.

la: quoniam multus sapientia Dei et fortis in potentia video omnis sine intermissio
en: For the wisdom of God is great, and he is strong in power, seeing all men without ceasing.

la: abeo ergo adulescens puer propheta Ramoth Galaad
en: So the young man, the servant of the prophet, went away to Ramoth Galaad,

la: et is qui adoro super tectum militia caelum et adoro et juro in Domino et juro in Melchom
en: And them that worship the host of heaven upon the top of houses, and them that adore, and swear by the Lord, and swear by Melchom.

la: de tribus autem Aser Masal et Abdon
en: And of the tribe of Aser, Masal and Abdon,

la: neque quisquam sum qui non in meus sum potestas vel non trado ego praeter tu qui uxor is sum quomodo ergo possum malus hic facio et peccaris in Deum meus
en: Neither is there any thing which is not in my power, or that he hath not delivered to me, but thee, who art his wife; how then can I do this wicked thing, and sin against my God?

la: sed loquor Dei sapientia in mysterium qui abs-condio sum quam praedestino Deus ante saeculum in gloria noster
en: But we speak the wisdom of God in a mystery, a wisdom which is hidden, which God ordained before the world, unto our glory:

la: sepelio autem omnis populus terra et sum is nomino dies in qui glorifico sum aio Dominus Deus
en: And all the people of the land shall bury him, and it shall be unto them a noted day, wherein I wa glorified, saith the Lord God.

la: scio enim qui praecipio do tu per Dominum Iesus
en: For you know what precept I have given to you by the Lord Jesus.

la: qui etiam Filio suus non parco sed pro nos omnis trado ille quomodo non etiam cum ille omnis nos dono
en: He that spared not even his own Son, but delivered him up for u all, how hath he not also, with him, given u all things?

la: ipse autem sicut Adam transgredior sum paciscor ibi praevarico sum in ego
en: But they, like Adam, have transgressed the covenant, there have they dealt treacherously against me.

la: cognosco ergo turba multus ex Judaeus quia illic sum et venio non propter Iesus tantus sed ut Lazaris video qui suscito ab morior
en: A great multitude therefore of the Jews knew that he wa there; and they came, not for Jesus' sake only, but that they might see Lazarus, whom he had raised from the dead.

la: recordor autem Deus Noe cunctus animo et omnis iumentum qui sum cum is in arca adduco spiritus super terra et imminutus sum aqua
en: And God remembered Noe, and all the living creatures, and all the cattle which were with him in the ark, and brought a wind upon the earth, and the water were abated.

la: et pono omnis qui audio in cor suus dico quis puto puer iste sum etenim manus Domini sum cum ille
en: And all they that had heard them laid them up in their heart, saying: What an one, think ye, shall this child be? For the hand of the Lord wa with him.

la: scribo tu pater quoniam cognosco is qui ab initium sum scribo tu adulescens quoniam vinco malignus
en: I write unto you, fathers, because you have known him who is from the beginning. I write unto you, young men, because you have overcome the wicked one.

la: et audio rex Ioachim et omnis potens et princeps is verbum hic et quaero rex interficio is et audio Urias et timeo fugio et ingredior sum Aegyptus
en: And Joakim, and all his men in power, and his prince heard these words: and the king sought to put him to death. And Urias heard it, and wa afraid, and fled and went into Egypt.

la: gaudeo qui in omnis confido in tu
en: I rejoice that in all thing I have confidence in you.

la: Moses famulus Domini et filius Israhel percutio is trado terra is Moses in possessio Rubenitis et Gadditis et dimidia tribuo Manasse
en: Moses the servant of the Lord, and the child of Israel slew them, and Moses delivered their land in possession to the Rubenites, and Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasses.

la: filius Pharus duo mille centum septuaginta duo
en: The child of Pharos, two thousand one hundred seventy-two.

la: et facio sum vereor in oblivio et qui recedo ab malus praeda pateo et video Dominus et malus appareo in oculus is quia non sum iudicium
en: And truth hath been forgotten: and he that departed from evil, lay open to be a prey: and the Lord saw, and it appeared evil in his eyes, because there is no judgment.

la: quare nos facio ascendo de Aegyptus et adduco in locus iste malus qui sero non possum qui neque ficus gigno neque vinea neque malus granatus insuper et aqua non habeo ad bibo
en: Why have you made u come up out of Egypt, and have brought u into this wretched place which cannot be sowed, nor bringeth forth figs, nor vines, nor pomegranates, neither is there any water to drink?

la: natio ex longinquus ad tu venio et munus defero adoro Dominum in tu et terra tuus in sanctificatio habeo
en: Nations from afar shall come to thee: and shall bring gifts, and shall adore the Lord in thee, and shall esteem thy land a holy.

la: Iesus ergo rursum fremo in sui ipse venio ad monumentum sum autem spelunca et lapis superpono sum is
en: Jesus therefore again groaning in himself, cometh to the sepulchre. Now it wa a cave; and a stone wa laid over it.

la: et objurgo optimas Judas et dico is qui sum res hic malus quam tu facio et profano dies sabbatum
en: And I rebuked the chief men of Juda, and said to them: What is this evil thing that you are doing, profaning the sabbath day:

la: Sed nos solus arceo ab religio proprietate.
en: But we alone are forbidden a religion of our own.

la: et quiesco facio multitudo canticus tuus et sono cithararis tuus non audio amplus
en: And I will make the multitude of thy song to cease, and the sound of thy harp shall be heard no more.

la: et alius angelus exeo de templum qui sum in caelum habeo et ipse falx acutus
en: And another angel came out of the temple which is in heaven, he also having a sharp sickle.

la: quando ob-sedeo civitas multus tempus et munitio circumdo ut expugno is non succido arbor de qui vesco possum neque securis per circumeo debeo vastaris regio quoniam lignum sum et non homo neque possum bellor contra tu augeo numerus
en: When thou hast besieged a city a long time, and hath compassed it with bulwarks, to take it, thou shalt not cut down the tree that may be eaten of, neither shalt thou spoil the country round about with axes: for it is a tree, and not a man, neither can it increase the number of them that fight against thee.

la: et dico propterea dico tu quia nemo possum venio ad ego nisi sum is do ab Patre meus
en: And he said: Therefore did I say to you that no man can come to me, unless it be given him by my Father.

la: et morior sum tertius pars creatura qui habeo anima et tertius pars navis intereo
en: And the third part of those creature died which had life in the sea: and the third part of the ship wa destroyed.

la: eicio ergo is de terra Aegyptius et educo in desertum
en: Therefore I brought them out from the land of Egypt, and brought them into the desert.

la: et dico omnis gens quare sic facio Dominus terra hic qui sum hic ira furor is immensus
en: And all the nation shall say: Why hath the Lord done thus to this land? what meaneth this exceeding great heat of his wrath?

la: et ut audio irascor sum et statim venio Ptolomaidam et scribo Ionathae ne obsido sed occurro sui ad colloquium festino
en: And when he heard it, he wa angry: and forthwith he came to Ptolemais, and wrote to Jonathan that he should not besiege the castle, but should come to him in haste, and speak to him.

la: Ner autem gigno Cos et Cos gigno Saul et Saul gigno Ionathan et Melchisuae et Abinadab et Esbaal
en: Now Ner begot Cis: and Cis begot Saul: and Saul begot Jonathan and Melchisua, and Abinadab, and Esbaal.

la: sepulcrum pateo sum guttur is lingua suus dolosus ago venenum aspis sub labium is
en: Their throat is an open sepulchre: with their tongue they have dealt deceitfully. The venom of asp is under their lips.

la: numquid gratia habeo servo ille quia facio qui sui impero non puto
en: Doth he thank that servant for doing the thing which he commanded him?

la: Cos in captivus saevio ab Germanis, praeclarus facinus auctor sum Caldus Caelius, adulescens vetustas familia suus dignissimus, qui complexus catenarum, qui vincio erat, seriem, ita ille inlisit caput suo, ut protinus pariter sanguis cerebrum effluvium expiraret.
en: When the Germans were venting their rage upon their captives, an heroic act wa performed by Caldus Caelius, a young man worthy in every way of his long line of ancestors, who, seizing a section of the chain with which he wa bound, brought it down with such force upon his own head a to cause his instant death, both his brain and his blood gushing from the wound.

la: qui cum audio Moses recipio satisfactio
en: Which when Moses had heard he wa satisfied.

la: facio ego sanctuarium et habito in medium is
en: And they shall make me a sanctuary, and I will dwell in the midst of them:

la: cum mane surgo egredior sum per desertum Thecuae proficio is sto Iosaphat in medium is dico audio ego Judas et omnis habitator Hierusal credo in Domino Deo vester et securus sum credo propheta is et cunctus evenio prosper
en: And they rose early in the morning, and went out through the desert of Thecua: and a they were marching, Josaphat standing in the midst of them, said: Hear me, ye men of Juda, and all the inhabitant of Jerusalem: believe in the Lord your God, and you shall be secure: believe his prophets, and all thing shall succeed well.

la: qui si urbs aliqui sum ingredior circumdo omnis Israhel civitas ille funis et traho is in torreo ut non repperiatur neque calculus quidem ex is
en: And if he shall enter into any city, all Israel shall cast rope round about that city, and we will draw it into the river, so that there shall not be found so much a one small stone thereof.

la: egredior sum post hic vir de domus Levi accipio uxor stirps suus
en: After this there went a man of the house of Levi; and took a wife of his own kindred.

la: unde facio sum ut hedum capraris accipio defero domus
en: Whereby it came to pass, that she received a young kid, and brought it home:

la: ante dies autem festus pascha scio Iesus quia venio is hora ut transeo ex hic mundus ad Patrem cum diligo suus qui sum in mundus in finis diligo is
en: Before the festival day of the pasch, Jesus knowing that his hour wa come, that he should pas out of this world to the Father: having loved his own who were in the world, he loved them unto the end.

la: et in domus per omnis regio is de filius Judas habito in Cariatharbe et in filiabus is et in Dibon et in filiabus is et in Capsel et in viculis is
en: And in the house through all their countries. Of the child of Juda some dwelt at Cariath-Arbe, and in the village thereof: and at Dibon, and in the village thereof: and at Cabseel, and in the village thereof.

la: et voco ego et loquor sum ad ego dico ecce qui egredior in terra aquilo requiesco facio spiritus meus in terra aquilo
en: And he called me, and spoke to me, saying: Behold they that go forth into the land of the north, have quieted my spirit in the land of the north.

la: quia timor qui timeo evenio ego et qui vereor accido
en: For the fear which I feared, hath come upon me: and that which I wa afraid of, hath befallen me.

la: et post obeo ille benedico Deus Isaac filius is qui habito iuxta puteus nomen Viventis et video
en: And after his death, God blessed Isaac his son, who dwelt by the well named Of the living and seeing.

la: corripio propior ne fors non dico et si dico ne fors itero
en: Reprove thy neighbour, for it may be he hath not said it: and if he hath said it, that he may not say it again.

la: saturo prior pro panis sui loco et famelicus saturo sum donec sterilis pario multus et qui multus habeo filius infirmo sum
en: They that were full before, have hired out themselves for bread: and the hungry are filled, so that the barren hath borne many: and she that had many child is weakened.

la: tu enim sum repromissio et filius vester et omnis qui longus sum quicumque advoco Dominus Deus noster
en: For the promise is to you and to your child and to all that are far off, whomsoever the Lord our God shall call.

la: Etrothsophan et Iazer Iecbaa
en: And Etroth, and Sophan, and Jazer, and Jegbaa,

la: quoniam autem sum filius mitto Deus Spiritum Filii suus in cor noster clamo Abba Pater
en: And because you are sons, God hath sent the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying: Abba, Father.

la: unus praeceptum sum atque iudicium tam tu quam advenio terra
en: There shall be all one law and judgment both for you and for them who are stranger in the land.

la: quia hic dico Dominus Deus gladius rex Babylon venio tu
en: For thus saith the Lord God: The sword of the king of Babylon shall come upon thee,

la: tunc dico is Iesus vado Satanas scribo sum Dominum Deum tuus adoro et ille solus servio
en: Then Jesus saith to him: Begone, Satan: for it is written: The Lord thy God shalt thou adore, and him only shalt thou serve.

la: cum autem offertor sacrificium coquo in clibanus de simila panis scilicet absque fermento conspergo oleum et laganum azymus oleum lito
en: But when thou offerest a sacrifice baked in the oven of flour, to wit, loaf without leaven, tempered with oil, and unleavened wafers, anointed with oil:

la: quidam quidem et propter invidia et contentio quidam autem et propter bonus voluntas Christus praedico
en: Some indeed, even out of envy and contention: but some also for good will preach Christ.

la: nam cum supervenio ille proelium et malus cogito post sui sacerdos ubi sui abscondo cum ille
en: For when war cometh upon them , or evils: the priest consult with themselves, where they may hide themselves with them.

la: Vinaceos cottidie recens succerno lectus restis subtento, vel cribrum ille res parato.
en: Sift the fresh husk daily through a bed stretched on cords, or make a sieve for the purpose,

la: si autem ille littera non credo quomodo meus verbum credo
en: But if you do not believe his writings, how will you believe my words?

la: Saul et Ionathan amabilis et decorus in vito suus in mors quoque non sum divido aquilis velox leo fortis
en: Saul and Jonathan, lovely, and comely in their life, even in death they were not divided: they were swifter than eagles, stronger than lions.

la: doctrina ora doctrina ora audio filius et qui custodio ille non periet in labium suus neque scandalizo in opus nequissimis
en: Hear, O ye children, the discipline of the mouth, and he that will keep it shall not perish by his lips, nor be brought to fall into most wicked works.

la: et exeo ab Pharao irascor nimis dico autem Dominus ad Mosen non audio tu Pharao ut multus signum fio in terra Aegyptius
en: And he went out from Pharao exceeding angry. But the Lord said to Moses: Pharao will not hear you, that many sign may be done in the land of Egypt.

la: et cum hic dico aio unde sum juvenis frater noster at ille dico ex tribus Nepthalim sum ex captivitas Ninus
en: And when he had spoken these words, he said: Whence are ye young men our brethren? But they said: We are of the tribe of Nephtali, of the captivity of Ninive.

la: Ne ille fallo sunt, qui divorto res pariter expectant, ignavia voluptas et praemium virtutis.
en: Surely they are deluded in looking forward with equal confidence to polar opposites, namely, the pleasure of idleness and the reward of merit.

la: si mortuus sum cum Christus ab elementum mundus quis adhuc tamquam vivo in mundus decerno
en: If then you be dead with Christ from the element of this world, why do you yet decree a though living in the world?

la: duo quoque vacca pinguis et quattuor aries occido facio et paro epulae omnis vicinus suus et cunctus amicus
en: He caused also two fat kine, and four wether to be killed, and a banquet to be prepared for all his neighbours, and all his friends,

la: eicio is extra foris domus pater suus et lapis obruo vir civitas is et morior quoniam facio nefas in Israhel ut fornicor in domus pater suus et aufero malus de medium tuus
en: They shall cast her out of the door of her father's house, and the men of the city shall stone her to death, and she shall die: because she hath done a wicked thing in Israel, to play the whore in her father's house: and thou shalt take away the evil out of the midst of thee.

la: Abimelech quoque audio vir turris Sycimorum pariter conglobo
en: Abimelech also hearing that the men of the tower of Sichem were gathered together,

la: Si sum non volet, do brassica coquo et panem, et bibo vinum lenis dilutum, lavo raro, uto unctione.
en: if he ha not, on boiled cabbage and bread. He should drink diluted mild wine, bathe rarely, and rub with oil.

la: mitto ergo David ad Thamar domus dico venio in domus Amnon frater tuus et facio is pulmentum
en: Then David sent home to Thamar, saying: Come to the house of thy brother Ammon, and make him a mess.

la: Illis etiam detraho caput in longus fortis pugno duro constantia et despero victoria in mors dimicabatur.
en: Even without their chief his men long continued to fight bravely, and despairing of victory they fought to the death.

la: et facio in Hierusal diverto genus machina qui in turris con-loco et in angulis murus ut mitto sagitto et saxum grandis egredior sum nomen is procul is qui auxilio is Dominus et corroboro ille
en: And he made in Jerusalem engine of diverse kinds, which he placed in the towers, and in the corner of the walls, to shoot arrows, and great stones: and his name went forth far abroad, for the Lord helped him, and had strengthened him.

la: FE aperio super nos os suus omnis inimicus
en: Phe. All our enemy have opened their mouth against us.

la: et sum ipse in puppis supra cervical dormio et excito is et dico is magister non ad tu pertineo quia pereo
en: And he wa in the hinder part of the ship, sleeping upon a pillow; and they awake him, and say to him: Master, doth, it not concern thee that we perish?

la: et dico servio David ad is ecce dies de qui loquor sum Dominus ad tu ego trado tu inimicus tuus ut facio is sicut placeo in oculus tuus surgo ergo David et praecido ora clamydis Saul silenter
en: And the servant of David said to him: Behold the day, of which the Lord said to thee: I will deliver thy enemy unto thee, that thou mayst do to him a it shall seem good in thy eyes. Then David arose, and secretly cut off the hem of Saul's robe.

la: P. Lucullus et L. Annius tribunus plebs resisto collega continuo magistratus nitebantur, qui dissensio totus annus comitium inpediebat.
en: The plebeian tribune Publius Lucullus and Lucius Annius, were striving to prolong their term of office in spite of the opposition of their colleagues, and this wrangling blocked the election of the whole year.

la: nullus enim audeo cubiculum virtus Assyrius pulso aut intro aperio
en: For no man durst knock, or open and go into the chamber of the general of the Assyrians.

la: Marius ad Zama pervenit.
en: Marius reached Zama.

la: immolo agnos ubi immolaris soleo hostia pro pecco et holocaustum is sum in locus sancio sicut enim pro pecco ita et pro delinquo ad sacerdos pertineo hostia sancio sancio sum
en: He shall immolate the lamb, where the victim for sin is wont to be immolated, and the holocaust, that is, in the holy place. For a that which is for sin, so also the victim for a trespass offering pertaineth to the priest: it is holy of holies.

la: in tempus quoque ille dico populus unusquisque cum puer suus maneo in medium Hierusal et sum tu vicis per nox et dies ad opero
en: At that time also I said to the people: Let every one with his servant stay in the midst of Jerusalem, and let u take our turn in the night, and by day, to work.

la: qui qui nosco loquor index justitia sum qui autem mentior testis sum fraudulentus
en: He that speaketh that which he knoweth, sheweth forth justice: but he that lieth, is a deceitful witness.

la: infernus subter conturbo sum in occurro advenio tuus suscito tu gigantas omnis princeps terra surgo de solium suus omnis princeps natio
en: Hell below wa in an uproar to meet thee at thy coming, it stirred up the giant for thee. All the prince of the earth are risen up from their thrones, all the prince of nations.

la: Facito rectus arbitratus dominus aut custodis, qui is negotium curabit.
en: Mill them honestly, to the satisfaction of the owner or his representative in charge of the work.

la: et cognosco Bacchis et dies sabbator venio ipse et omnis exercitus is trans Jordanes
en: And Bacchides understood it, and he came himself, with all his army, over the Jordan, on the sabbath day.

la: Video et theatrum neque singulus satis sum neque nuda; nam ne vel hiems voluptas impudicus frigeret, primus Lacedaemonius penulam ludus excogitaverunt.
en: I see theatres'and a single theatre here or there will not suffice'not uncovered, either. For'oh! it wa for the game that the Spartans first invented the cloak,c in case unclean pleasure should be cold in winter!
